Sentencas: Paper-fibres are studied for use as a pore-former to produce gas channels in the anode substrates of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Paper-Fibres Used as a Pore-Former for Anode Substrate of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: These fibres produce cylindrical pores within the anode substrate, which are different from the pores formed by the conventional pore-formers such as wheat flour and graphite.
Titulo: Paper-Fibres Used as a Pore-Former for Anode Substrate of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The cylindrical pores make it easier to connect each other to form continuous pathways for rapid gas diffusion.
Titulo: Paper-Fibres Used as a Pore-Former for Anode Substrate of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Paper-fibres can create more open porosity than the same amount of flour.
Titulo: Paper-Fibres Used as a Pore-Former for Anode Substrate of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The application of the paper-fibres significantly improves the cell performance by enhancing the gas diffusion process.
Titulo: Paper-Fibres Used as a Pore-Former for Anode Substrate of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The anode-supported YSZ film cells with 5 wt.-% and 10 wt.-% paper-fibres exhibit maximum power densities of 0.72 and 1.06 W cm(-2), respectively, using hydrogen as fuel and ambient air as oxidant at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Paper-Fibres Used as a Pore-Former for Anode Substrate of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
